      "writtenOn": "2020-07-27T23:05:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we have mostly empty queues, tail latency of a task processing will be high, since the task will need to win a lottery first to be picked up. Ideally each worker is assigned a subset of queues it *always* polls, in coordinated fashion so all queues are polled at all times.\n\nIn our situation its probably fine...",
